notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T09:43:46.651Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented createExtensionTestHarness + ExtensionTestHarness interface in src/sdk/testing.ts (re-exported via src/sdk/index.ts and the @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing subpath). The factory activates a module once and returns a fluent fixture whose 16 assert*/12 run* methods + deactivate() are pre-bound to the correct activation sub-registry; methods use closures (no `this`) so they are safe to destructure. Added 4 focused tests (sdk-index.spec.ts) covering every method via one rich fixture extension + a barrel-equivalence lock. testing.ts at 100/100/100/100 coverage (415 stmts, 287 branches, 158 fns). Docs updated: docs/SDK.md (recommended-entry paragraph + exports list + example) and docs/EXTENSIONS.md (in-place, under 450-line cap). typecheck + quality:static + quality:docs-skills green. Manual end-to-end smoke (temp dir, symlinked package, real @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing import) PASSED: assert/run/hook/importer/destructure/deactivate all work against the built dist."
close_reason: "Shipped createExtensionTestHarness: a fluent ExtensionTestHarness fixture that activates a module once and binds all 16 assert*/12 run* helpers + deactivate() to the correct activation sub-registry, so package authors never thread activation.registrations/.commands/.hooks by hand."
